Command Design Pattern ^yf6SSGSH


The Command Design Pattern is a behavioral design pattern that 
encapsulates a request as an object, thereby allowing 
parameterization of clients with queues, requests, and operations. 
This pattern decouples the sender of a request from its receiver, 
providing flexibility in handling the request. It also allows for the 
support of undoable operations, queuing of requests, logging changes
, etc. ^ApKlpq9C

public class LightOnCommand implements Command{
    Light light;
    public LightOnCommand(Light light){
        this.light = light;
    } 
    public void execute(){
        light.switchOn();
    }
    public void undo(){
        light.switchOff();
    }
} ^eELaztyD

public class Invoker{
    Command command;
    Stack<Command> history = new Stack<>();
    public void setCommand(Command command){
        this.command = command;
        history.push(command);
    }
    public void invoke(){
        command.execute();
    }
    public void undo{
        if(!history.isEmpty()){
            history.pop().undo();
        }
    }
} ^thsHSwy0
